From f3efbb38578ea978e19c341b853228db62bdc3cc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Yury Norov (NVIDIA)" <yury.norov@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Dec 2025 23:05:42 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] sched/fair: Drop useless cpumask_empty() in
 find_energy_efficient_cpu()

References: bsc#1234634 (Scheduler functional and performance backports SL-16.1)
Patch-mainline: v7.0-rc1
Git-commit: ff1de90dd7a69ef43586683535ad87ab899a1214

cpumask_empty() call is O(N) and useless because the previous
cpumask_and() returns false for empty 'cpus'. Drop it.

Signed-off-by: Yury Norov (NVIDIA) <yury.norov@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Peter Zijlstra (Intel) <peterz@infradead.org>
Reviewed-by: Madadi Vineeth Reddy <vineethr@linux.ibm.com>
Reviewed-by: K Prateek Nayak <kprateek.nayak@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Vincent Guittot <vincent.guittot@linaro.org>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20251207040543.407695-1-yury.norov@gmail.com
Signed-off-by: Mel Gorman <mgorman@suse.de>
---
 kernel/sched/fair.c | 4 +---
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/fair.c b/kernel/sched/fair.c
index 209dc8926341..1b35295928c0 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/fair.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/fair.c
@@ -8456,9 +8456,7 @@ static int find_energy_efficient_cpu(struct task_struct *p, int prev_cpu)
 		int max_spare_cap_cpu = -1;
 		int fits, max_fits = -1;
 
-		cpumask_and(cpus, perf_domain_span(pd), cpu_online_mask);
-
-		if (cpumask_empty(cpus))
+		if (!cpumask_and(cpus, perf_domain_span(pd), cpu_online_mask))
 			continue;
 
 		/* Account external pressure for the energy estimation */
